# About OrionHealth

## Our Story

OrionHealth began with a simple observation: **health data is fragmented, siloed, and often inaccessible to the people who need it most**.

Modern healthcare generates vast amounts of data — electronic health records, lab results, medical imaging, wearable device readings — yet patients often struggle to access their own information. We believe technology should **empower individuals**, not create new barriers.

## The Problem

### Fragmentation
Medical data is scattered across multiple healthcare providers, hospitals, clinics, and personal devices.

### Privacy Concerns
Sharing health data raises legitimate privacy concerns. Current systems often lack granular consent mechanisms.

### Access Inequality
In many parts of the world, accessing healthcare means navigating paper-based systems.

## Our Solution

### 1. Patient-Centric Data Ownership
OrionHealth stores all data on the user's device. You own your health records — not hospitals, not insurers, not tech companies.

### 2. Privacy by Design
Every feature in OrionHealth is designed with privacy first:
- **Zero-knowledge architecture**: Your data is encrypted, and we can't read it
- **Local AI processing**: Medical AI runs on your device
- **Explicit consent**: Every data sharing action requires your approval

### 3. Standards-Based Interoperability
We implement medical standards correctly:
- **ICD-10**: Disease classification for diagnoses
- **LOINC**: Laboratory observations and measurements
- **SNOMED CT**: Clinical terminology

## Technology Choices

| Component | Technology |
|-----------|------------|
| Framework | Flutter 3.x |
| Database | Isar (local, encrypted) |
| AI | Gemma 4B GGUF + Ollama |
| Encryption | AES-256-GCM, Argon2id |
| BLE | flutter_blue_plus 2.3.1 |
| Standards | ICD-10, LOINC, SNOMED CT |

## Milestones

| Date | Milestone |
|------|----------|
| 2024 Q1 | Project inception, initial architecture design |
| 2024 Q2 | First functional prototype with encrypted local storage |
| 2024 Q3 | BLE sharing implementation |
| 2024 Q4 | AI assistant integration, Gemma 4B GGUF support |
| 2025 Q1 | Medical standards integration |
| 2025 Q2 | Professional UI redesign |
| 2025 Q3 | Privacy-first analytics, community features |

## The Name

**Orion** — the hunter constellation visible worldwide — represents our vision: a guiding presence in the complex landscape of personal health management.

## Open Source

OrionHealth is and will remain open source. We believe healthcare technology should be auditable and community contributions improve quality.

## Future Vision

### Short Term
- iOS support
- Health insurance integration
- Telemedicine appointment scheduling

### Long Term
- Decentralized health records network
- AI-powered health insights
- Integration with national health systems

